- ## Concepts
#Concepts #Analysis #UserCentered #Design #Software #Product #Management 
Mental Models guide the actions of what to do next in order to arrive at specific goals and guides a user’s reasoning and beliefs of what to do in unexpected situations. If there is a significant mismatch between a user’s Mental Model and the conceptual model underlying the operating of a system, interaction is likely to break down.

- ## Concepts
#Concepts #Analysis #UserCentered #Design #Software #Product #Management 
Norman (1983) refers to conceptual models as tools for the understanding and teaching of physical models. Picking up the differentiation between conceptual and Mental Models, an important prerequi- site for successful user interfaces is to base the design on a coherent and graspable (but not necessarily physically correct) conceptual model to induce a stable Mental Model in congruence with a user’s understanding of the task.
